China Stocks May Drop on Investment, Growth Concern, Citic Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-10-24T01:01:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-24/china-stocks-may-drop-on-investment-growth-concern-citic-says.html
 China’s stocks may drop as property
investment is likely to slump and investors are “pessimistic”
about the “lack of new drivers” for long-term economic growth,
according to Citic Securities Co.  The brokerage recommends “low-valuation” stocks such as
banks, coal producers and automakers, Chen Hualiang, a Citic
analyst, wrote in a report today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  